<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-634-771  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 634 771.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>EDN  Oct 25 1990 v35 n22 p130(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Low-cost industrial PC family draws little power and fits in asmall space. (Octagon Systems Corp's Micro-C family of board-levelIBM PC-compatible microcomputers)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Leibson, Steven H.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Octagon Systems Corp (Westminster, CO) offers the Micro-PC familyof compact, rugged (-20 to +70 degrees C), low-power and low-costboard-level IBM PC-compatible microcomputers and support cards forindustrial applications.andP;  The embedded PCs feature a non-standard4.9-by-4.2-inch form factor supported by proprietary card cagescontaining back planes and power supplies.andP;  The Micro-PC cardsinclude the $195 Model 5000 PC control card, which features a10MHz NEC V20 microprocessor (MPU), BIOS ROM, watchdog timer,8-bit IBM PC bus, and sockets for single-inline memory module(SIMM) and either a 1M-bit flash EPROM or static RAM chip.andP;  The$345 Model 5010 adds one parallel and two serial ports.andP;  Supportcards include $295 Model 5400 EGA card, $195 Model 5800 diskcontroller card, $195 Model 5300 counter/timer input/output (I/O)card, $195 Model 5600 digital I/O card, and two $395motion-control cards.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Octagon Systems Corp. (Products).andO;Product:   Octagon Systems Micro PC (Microcomputer) (Design andconstruction).andO;Topic:     Embedded SystemsSpecificationsSizeApplicationsI/O Boards/CardsSpecial-Purpose ComputersMicrocomputers.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>